      <section eId="sec_11_3_501">
        <num>11-3-501</num>
        <content>
          <p>Exhibit the instrument;</p>
          <p>Give reasonable identification and, if presentment is made on behalf of another person, reasonable evidence of authority to do so; and</p>
          <p>Sign a receipt on the instrument for any payment made or surrender the instrument if full payment is made.</p>
          <p>Return the instrument for lack of a necessary indorsement; or</p>
          <p>Refuse payment or acceptance for failure of the presentment to comply with the terms of the instrument, an agreement of the parties, or other applicable law or rule.</p>
        </content>
